      "comment": "HOPE MOO MOO (7) turned in a solid run last start over 390m at this track finishing 4th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (22.11). Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. LADY DREAMER (8) struggled to get involved last start after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 1.3 lengths at this track (19.60) beating Rainmaker Joe in a Restricted WIN on March 11. Should be in this for a long way. KEY CHANGE (4) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage third, beaten 3.5 lengths (19.97) at this track in a Grade 5 over 352m. Will give a great sight again. GEMSTONE JASPER (6) is in the mix after placing last time out.",
